post_text: Crawford County High School Football coaching staff would like to invite any and all students in grades 2nd-6th grade to join us for a series of youth football camps. These camps will be held Saturday September 12th and Saturday September 19th with the potential of a few more if there is enough interest. These camps will run from 10:00am-12:00pm at the High School Football Field. Every student must bring a facemask and a water bottle. A snack will be provided to each student and water stations will be set up for refills. Please contact Coach Bell at tbell@cccs.k12.in.us for more information.

shared_text:
South Crawford Elementary School
July 31 at 6:36 PM ·

Please read the following information regarding virtual learners:

Who: ELEMENTARY Virtual Parents ONLY

When: Thursday, August 6th @ 4:30

or

Thursday, August 6th @ 6:00

Where: Crawford County High School Cafeteria

Parents will pick up their child’s chromebook and CCCS staff will provide a brief tutorial on the expectations of our virtual students and parents. The staff will help parents log into their child’s Google Classroom and help them become familiar with navigating the site and learning about the other online resources the teachers will be utilizing to enhance your child’s education.

Parents will have the opportunity to purchase insurance on the device for $25. Please be aware that you will be responsible for the cost of replacing the device if you do not purchase the insurance and the device is damaged.

Masks are required. Only one adult per family should attend. Students do not need to attend.

Flyers coming home soon....

Looking for an opportunity to send your kids to college? Ivy Tech Community College in Sellersburg is offering a unique program this winter that is geared for students in Kindergarten through 5th grade. There are exciting, high interest classes such as, Cooking, Lego Robotics, Science, Art and more! The class times are from 9:00 AM to 4:00 PM on Dec. 20th and 21st. Visit connect.ivytech.edu/kidscollege for more details. We are eager to open new horizons for your child!
